      "content": "Substantive due process is the essential engine of American progress because it allows the Constitution to breathe life into unspoken rights that are necessary for a free society, such as the right to marry, access to abortion, and the right to control one's own body. Without this judicial tool, the written text of the Constitution would be a static document that fails to protect the evolving needs and dignity of future generations. It empowers the courts to stand as the ultimate guardians of liberty, ensuring that the government cannot infringe upon fundamental human freedoms simply because those specific words were never explicitly drafted into the legal code.",
      "source": "target",
